            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely dice the<strong> onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong>, roughly chop the <strong>cherry</strong> <strong>tomatoes</strong> and top, tail and grate the <strong>carrot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Return the reserved pan to a medium-high heat with a little drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and once hot, add the <strong>chopped onion </strong>and <strong>garlic</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to soften</p><p>Once softened, add the <strong>chopped tomatoes</strong>,<strong> grated carrot</strong> and<strong> dried oregano</strong> with 1/2 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tsp] </span><strong>flour</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 6-8 min or until softened</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1646740905539-x200.jpg",
