    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dissolve the <strong>beef stock</strong> <strong>mix</strong> and <strong>tomato paste</strong> in 300ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [500ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>– this is your<strong> tomato stock</strong></p><p>Once the vegetables have softened, add the <strong>tomato stock</strong> and cook for 4-5 min further or until the sauce has slightly thickened</p><p>Once slightly thickened, pour the sauce over the meatballs<strong> </strong>and put the dish in the oven for 15-20 min<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>or until the meatballs are browned and cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
